        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "7638c41913e09b3a",
        "text": "The entity system is grounded in three\nprinciples. - First, an entity can incorporate anywhere, regardless of the\nlocation of its operations. - Second, an entity chartered in one jurisdiction can\ndo business in virtually any other jurisdiction. - Third, while operating in those other jurisdictions, the entity continues to be governed by the entity\nlaw under which it was formed. "
      },
      "date": 1519633497701
